review_blob: This was poured at beer geeks in highland Indiana. This is a typical saison/farmhouse ale. It has a light fruit smell and the taste is a strong mix of fruit flavors that muddle together.
It is a decent Stout. Pours dark. Very bitter and light chocolate taste. Overall I enjoyed the beer.

Beer poured  a dark ruby with a large white head. Initially there was an aroma of fruits. First tasting had hints of  fruit and a slight coffee flavor.  Little bitter on the end of the taste. This is a beer that I will come back to.
Pours golden. Strong citrus smell. You can taste the light hops, with a taste of citrus.
It poured a deep brown, with small head. Had a very light smell to it. The taste felt watered down, with light roasted coffee and a slight tart finish. Overall I would ahve this again.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. It poured a dark brown. It had a strong coffee and dark chocolate aroma and taste.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. Had a very strong coffee and chocolate aroma. The taste was a bitter strong coffee. Overall a great beer.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. Batch 1. Poured a brown color. The aroma was a strong citrus. Its taste was very hoppy and bitter. With a taste of coffee as well.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. Batch 4. Poured a light brown color. Had a caramel aroma. Taste was a very strong coffee bean.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. Batch 7. Strong fruit flavor, sweet aroma. Overall a good beer.
@ Immy Backyard Throwdown. Pours a dark brown. Smell was a dark chocolate cherry. Awesome. Had a sweet taste of chocolate and fruit. Overall a great beer. I would have again.

Bottle #09752 of 11950 shared by Immy at Immys Backyard Throwdown. Pours a light yellow. First taste had a light fruit, slight bitter but smooth overall impression. It was one that I would have again.

750 mL bottle shared by dkachur at Immys Backyard Throwdown. Pours a light yellow. Smell is a strong apple. It tasted very light apple with a tart finish in there. It was a good break at the throwdown. I enjoyed it and would drink it again.
Strong aroma of citrus when poured. Had a taste of fruit at the front, then a slight bitter finish.

Shared by Immy at Immys Backyard Throwdown.  Well it pours like a light yellow. Nothing impressive or even decent about it. I would never recommend this to anyone. Mad props to dkachur for using Skanky in a review.

Bottle shared by dkachur at Immys Backyard Throwdown. This was batch 777. Strong smell of bourbon. There is a slight cherry taste, as well as a roasted coffee and bourbon. I overall enjoyed this and will drink it again.
beer_name: Bells Cherry Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: 750 mL bottle shared by Immy at Immys Backyard Throwdown. Poured clear gold with no head. It had a strong wine smell to it. It had a strong apple taste to it with a slight bitter finish. Overall a good cider that I would have again
Poured dark with very little to no head. The aroma was light coffee with milk. Taste like coffee with creamer that the beans were roasted first. Slight bitter after taste but not over whelming.
Aroma is exactly like a chai tea or pumpkin roll. Taste is also comparable to both, with a slight bitter taste in the middle. It isnt to overwhelming. I enjoy it and would have it again.
Poured nice dark brown, very little head to it. First taste, slight grainy, bitter at the beginning but easy to drink. Taste of roasted coffee. Overall a good beer, that I would drink again.

This was a great beer for me.  I had it on tap at FFF, and I was surprised when the bartender suggested it once I told him I am into doppelbocks. I have to admit it was a great choice. Light in color and great tasting. It had a light fruit flavor to it. Great beer.
On tap at FFF, it poured a light red with a small head. Had a sweet banana bread taste to it. Very good beer and one I will drink again.
UPDATED: JUL 20, 2009
This was a great beer, strong citrus smell to it. Light carmel taste as well as a fruit after-taste. Overall a great beer. I poured it from the bottle.
This beer had a very sweet aroma, poured dark brown. It had a very large white head. I liked the taste at first, but the after taste was far to bitter for my taste.

This beer was just my taste. It had a nice thick head to it. Poured a nice brownish color. It had a very sweet smell to it. Also had a very sweet taste to it, rasin, fruit and toffee. Very smooth going down, and a sweet after taste.
2004 bottle- Poured a dark brownish red. Very thick head. It had a very sweet taste and smell. I would recommend this beer to anyone.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob: Poured out hazy golden color, had a citrus smell to it. Very strong sweet wheat taste to it. Overall I would recommend it to anyone.

It pour a beautiful dark brown/black, also had a thick brown head that settled to a pure white. It had a very full bodied taste. Tastes of carmel and mocha. Slight bitter finish but not over bearing at all.
It poured very dark brown/black. It had a dark brown head to it. There was a strong aroma of fruit. It tastes like mocha/chocolate, with a bitter finish.

I had high hopes for this beer, knowing the history. When poured it was a nice golden color and very little head. It smelled delightful. I like the taste of fruits and honey while drinking it. The aftertaste of saffron was a bit to much for me. This is a good beer but doesnt match what I am looking for at this time.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: I tried this the other night at a local bar, I loved it so much I had to find it again. It has a very cloudy golden red tint to it. I tastes just like it smells, kinda fruity with a slight bitter finish to it.
Bottle: It is clear golden brown when poured. Had a lot of head to it. It has a slight sour taste to it, and also a subtle fruity taste.
